WEBVTT

00:11.637 --> 00:14.879
[CHATTERING]

00:20.812 --> 00:23.303
MAN 1: Would you like to try a lumiere?
MAN 2: I'd like to.

00:23.482 --> 00:25.188
MAN 1:
They're great.

00:31.365 --> 00:33.196
WOMAN 1:
It's delicious. Didn't I tell you?

00:33.367 --> 00:35.949
WOMAN 2: Would you like a lumiere?
MAN 3: Fresh picked.

00:41.583 --> 00:44.325
WOMAN 3:
A new arrival. Step back.

00:55.514 --> 00:56.879
Ohh.

00:57.683 --> 01:00.595
-| feel nauseous.
CLAUDINE: It'll pass.

01:01.520 --> 01:03.511
Well done. As you were.

01:03.689 --> 01:07.523
Wait. Are you like the head
of the fairies or something?

01:07.693 --> 01:10.275
Oh, hardly. No, I'm your--

01:10.445 --> 01:12.572
I'm your godmother.
You know, it's a--

01:12.739 --> 01:14.855
l have a fairy godmother?

01:15.033 --> 01:19.026
It's not all fun and parties.
Some of us have to work.

01:19.204 --> 01:22.367
Okay, if yourjob is to look after me,
can ljust say you suck?

01:22.541 --> 01:25.283
You know how many times
I could have used a fairy godmother?

01:25.460 --> 01:26.870
Well, you're still alive.

01:27.045 --> 01:29.377
You're not exactly Miss Trouble Free,
you know.

01:29.548 --> 01:33.382
Come on. Let's enjoy the party.

01:35.887 --> 01:37.878
SooMe?

01:39.224 --> 01:40.430
-Barry?
BARRY: Yeah.

01:40.601 --> 01:42.091
-The bellboy?
-Yeah.

01:42.269 --> 01:44.555
-How long have you been here?
-We just got here.

01:44.730 --> 01:49.645
Jesus, can you believe this place?
Oh, this is my fairy godmother, Lloyd.

01:49.860 --> 01:51.225
Hi.

01:52.112 --> 01:53.648
Look at everyone.

01:53.864 --> 01:56.856
Do you realize this is like the one place
in the universe where we're not freaks?

01:57.034 --> 01:58.069
[CLAUDINE CHUCKLES]

01:58.243 --> 02:03.078
Well, we're going to get a drink.
Once you two are finished chatting, mingle.

02:04.875 --> 02:08.459
Would you like a lumiere?
A light-fruit.

02:10.422 --> 02:12.458
Yeah.

02:13.592 --> 02:15.503
WOMAN:
Oh, my God.

02:17.220 --> 02:18.551
Mm.

02:21.975 --> 02:24.466
Barry, hold on a sec.

02:25.145 --> 02:29.514
Whoa. This is like biting
into pure happiness.

02:29.691 --> 02:33.104
-You gotta try this, Sookie.
-Yeah, hold on.

02:38.784 --> 02:41.196
Now, isn't that a beauty?

02:41.536 --> 02:43.788
Just turned ripe.

02:53.924 --> 02:55.414
Granddaddy?

02:57.803 --> 02:59.543
Beg your pardon?

02:59.721 --> 03:01.461
Granddaddy Earl.

03:03.809 --> 03:05.800
I'm Sookie.

03:12.484 --> 03:14.645
| just saw you last week.

03:15.529 --> 03:17.315
It was your birthday.

03:18.323 --> 03:21.815
Granddaddy,
that was 20 years ago.

04:58.298 --> 05:00.584
Oh, my Lord. lt's....

05:01.593 --> 05:04.130
Your grandma, did she--?

05:05.847 --> 05:11.308
-Did she pass gentle?
-It was peaceful.

05:11.478 --> 05:13.935
She lived a happy life.

05:14.105 --> 05:19.316
Mama and Daddy, they were in a flood,
so I have no idea.

05:19.486 --> 05:23.650
I try not to think about it.
It's just me and Jason now.

05:26.451 --> 05:29.818
Twenty years.
I can't understand how--

05:29.996 --> 05:32.783
I swear I've only been here
a few hours.

05:32.958 --> 05:36.997
-You've been here all this time?
-|....

05:38.839 --> 05:41.831
I must have lost track of time.

05:42.843 --> 05:45.960
It's just everything seems so....

05:47.138 --> 05:48.969
Lovely.

05:49.140 --> 05:51.222
[GROWLING]

05:54.187 --> 05:56.303
WOMAN:
Would you like a lumiere?

06:00.443 --> 06:02.104
SOOKIE:
Granddaddy, can you hear me?

06:03.613 --> 06:05.444
EARL:
Yes. Yes, I can hear you.

06:05.615 --> 06:09.153
SOOKIE:
This is a trap. We need to leave.

06:11.538 --> 06:13.824
MAB:
A trap?

06:16.001 --> 06:18.743
The trap is the world you've left behind.

06:21.172 --> 06:23.663
Oh, no need to bow.
We're all friends here.

06:24.843 --> 06:28.335
I'm sorry.
I just have no idea who you are.

06:28.513 --> 06:31.846
You can call me Mab.
I am the one who sent for you.

06:33.268 --> 06:35.350
Have you had a try
of the lumiere fruit yet?

06:35.520 --> 06:37.727
-No, I haven't.
-|t's very good. Have a taste.

06:37.898 --> 06:39.684
I don't want any!

06:41.443 --> 06:43.934
The future of our kind is in peril.

06:44.154 --> 06:48.022
A vampire breached our realm
because he'd had a taste of fairy blood.

06:48.199 --> 06:50.030
Your blood.

06:50.201 --> 06:53.364
In the old kingdom,
vampires nearly drank us to extinction.

06:53.538 --> 06:56.075
-They drove us onto this plane.
-It won't happen again.

06:56.249 --> 06:58.865
I'm staying away from vampires.
l guaran-damn-tee you.

06:59.044 --> 07:00.250
[lN DEEP VOICE]
Oh, I know.

07:00.420 --> 07:03.878
[IN NORMAL VOICE] We can't have bearers
of the fae on the human plane any longer.

07:04.049 --> 07:07.541
We've sown too many seeds with humans.
Now it is time to harvest.

07:08.553 --> 07:09.713
Harvest?

07:12.807 --> 07:15.890
-You're harvesting people.
-Fruit, please.

07:17.395 --> 07:19.386
Get away from me!

07:20.231 --> 07:21.562
MAB [IN DEEP VOICE]:
Eat it.

07:22.192 --> 07:24.057
[SOOKIE GRUNTS AND SCREAMS]

07:28.615 --> 07:30.480
[MAB SCREAMS]

07:32.452 --> 07:34.909
[CROWD CLAMORS AND GASPS]

07:38.917 --> 07:40.453
Granddaddy, run!

07:43.755 --> 07:45.962
Do not let the girl escape!

07:52.639 --> 07:54.470
Get her!

07:58.520 --> 08:00.351
-Can you keep up?
-Ah! Trying.

08:00.522 --> 08:01.932
Try harder!

08:04.651 --> 08:07.267
CLAUDE:
Come with us! We can help you!

08:07.445 --> 08:09.527
SOOKIE:
Let me go!

08:12.450 --> 08:16.034
Do not fear. We can get you home.
Hold them off!

08:16.246 --> 08:21.366
I've got the humans!
Hurry. This way! Hurry!

08:36.182 --> 08:37.763
This way!

08:42.063 --> 08:43.803
You have to jump.

08:43.982 --> 08:46.143
What? I don't even know
who the hell you are.

08:46.317 --> 08:48.854
My sister abducted you
because the crown wishes...

08:49.029 --> 08:51.315
...to seal off the human world
from Fairy forever.

08:51.489 --> 08:53.980
-And you don't?
-It was once our world too.

08:54.159 --> 08:57.367
It is our right to travel there.
Have you eaten the light-fruit?

08:57.537 --> 09:00.153
-He has, but not me.
-Only you can go then.

09:03.001 --> 09:04.332
-Hurry!
MAB: Humans!

09:04.502 --> 09:07.994
Do not listen to his lies.
Jump and you will die!

09:11.593 --> 09:15.427
She's closing the portal.
Do you want to go home or not?

09:16.681 --> 09:18.922
Sookie, go! Go! Sookie!

09:19.100 --> 09:20.340
[SOOKIE SCREAMS]

09:24.439 --> 09:25.804
[BOTH GRUNT]

09:36.534 --> 09:38.195
Granddaddy?

09:41.456 --> 09:42.696
What's wrong?

09:42.874 --> 09:47.117
lt's-- I had the light-fruit.

09:48.546 --> 09:50.707
But I had to see you home.

09:52.884 --> 09:55.045
Your....

09:55.220 --> 09:57.051
Your mama and daddy.

09:59.724 --> 10:01.885
Your granny, are they here?

10:02.060 --> 10:03.891
Yes. Come on.

10:08.817 --> 10:10.648
[GROANING]

10:21.079 --> 10:22.569
I never meant to leave you all.

10:24.082 --> 10:26.744
We never believed you abandoned us.

10:27.460 --> 10:29.667
None of us ever stopped loving you.

10:29.838 --> 10:31.703
That's good.

10:32.757 --> 10:34.839
Your gran's gonna give me
what for in heaven.

10:35.135 --> 10:37.376
I guarantee you.

10:44.435 --> 10:47.723
-l'm dying, pumpkin.
-Granddaddy, no.

10:47.897 --> 10:49.603
I can feel it.

10:54.779 --> 10:56.770
Give this to Jason.

10:57.740 --> 11:00.482
Man ought to own a good watch.

11:00.952 --> 11:03.113
Now I'm happy.

11:03.288 --> 11:05.620
I'm where I belong.

11:06.124 --> 11:09.491
You be good, Sookie. I love you.

11:39.365 --> 11:42.823
[MEN CHATTERING
& TOOLS HAMMERING]

11:45.455 --> 11:46.991
SOOKIE:
What the--?

11:58.009 --> 12:00.842
Sweetheart,
where do you think you're going?

12:01.012 --> 12:03.674
-|t's my house.
-Hey, you can't go in there.

12:08.686 --> 12:10.847
SOOKIE:
Oh, my God.

12:14.192 --> 12:16.023
Um, excuse me.

12:16.194 --> 12:19.061
Honey, if you don't come back out,
I'm calling the police.

12:19.239 --> 12:24.029
Do it. Call the cops.
Because I would love an explanation.

12:49.060 --> 12:50.891
JASON:
Hello.

12:52.730 --> 12:54.470
Police.

12:56.734 --> 12:58.725
Jason?

13:02.365 --> 13:04.731
SooMe.SooMe.

13:04.909 --> 13:07.742
Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

13:09.289 --> 13:11.200
Look. I can't believe it's you.

13:11.374 --> 13:13.581
Jason, why are you dressed like a cop?

13:13.751 --> 13:15.867
Jesus Christ.
We thought you were dead.

13:16.045 --> 13:19.583
We've been looking everywhere for you.
We figured a vampire must have did it.

13:19.757 --> 13:22.419
Bill or maybe that crazy tall one.

13:22.593 --> 13:25.426
Hold on, hold on. Stop a second.

13:25.596 --> 13:27.427
What is today's date?

13:27.598 --> 13:30.260
Today is October 21st.

13:30.435 --> 13:32.096
I've been gone two weeks?

13:33.938 --> 13:35.394
Sook.

13:36.441 --> 13:40.025
You've been gone 12 and a half months.

13:44.449 --> 13:48.488
SOOKIE: You sold my house?
-Your stuff's all still here.

13:48.661 --> 13:52.279
Now, I packed it,
but I didn't get a chance to....

13:52.457 --> 13:54.118
Yeah, I saw.

13:54.292 --> 13:56.123
Well, at least I didn't throw it away.

13:56.294 --> 13:58.956
Look, Sook, you have been gone
for a year...

13:59.130 --> 14:01.792
...and it killed me
even thinking about all the people...

14:01.966 --> 14:05.458
...who should still be living here
and how they're all gone.

14:05.636 --> 14:09.800
-| just couldn't take it no more.
-Who bought the place?

14:09.974 --> 14:12.465
A real estate company
with a bunch of initials.

14:12.643 --> 14:15.635
AIK I think.
Look, they had the cash.

14:15.813 --> 14:18.850
They was offering more
than I was asking, and ljust....

14:19.067 --> 14:20.807
| just wanted to be done with it.

14:20.985 --> 14:24.318
-I can't believe you gave up on me.
-What choice did I have?

14:24.489 --> 14:28.528
Sook, you ain't the type
to just skip off without telling no one.

14:28.701 --> 14:30.817
Plus, you'd been
all mixed up with vampires.

14:30.995 --> 14:33.828
Look, we put up fliers.
We called TV stations.

14:33.998 --> 14:38.207
I did everything I could think of.
We even made up a website.

14:38.378 --> 14:40.869
But after you were gone so long....

14:41.089 --> 14:45.207
I swear it felt like 10,
15 minutes at the most.

14:45.385 --> 14:48.843
The place where I went,
time just works differently.

14:51.391 --> 14:52.801
I believe you.

14:52.975 --> 14:55.717
I do, but, Sook,
if you start telling people...

14:55.895 --> 15:00.184
...that you time traveled
to a land full of fairies...

15:00.358 --> 15:02.849
...they're gonna put you away.

15:09.700 --> 15:11.361
Where the hell did you get that?

15:11.536 --> 15:15.199
I saw Granddaddy. He was there.

15:15.373 --> 15:17.659
He wanted you to have it.

15:17.834 --> 15:20.997
He swore
he'd only been there a few hours.

15:21.170 --> 15:24.754
Jason,helooked
just like we remember him.

15:28.219 --> 15:30.835
Time stands still there,
and no one knows it.

15:31.013 --> 15:35.382
It's how I lost a year of my life
and Granddaddy lost 20.

15:35.560 --> 15:37.346
Where is he?

15:37.520 --> 15:40.353
Well, you didn't leave him there, did you?

15:40.523 --> 15:43.640
Jason, he's gone. I'm sorry.

15:46.070 --> 15:48.857
But he wanted you to have that watch...

15:49.031 --> 15:53.024
...so that you'd always know
that he never meant to leave you.

16:00.751 --> 16:03.367
What time you got?

16:03.546 --> 16:05.161
Six thirty-five.

16:08.301 --> 16:10.917
Which means....

16:24.400 --> 16:25.981
My God.

16:26.194 --> 16:27.809
SooMe.

16:31.199 --> 16:33.611
Forgive me. I know I'm not welcome.

16:34.076 --> 16:37.443
l have not felt your presence
for over a year.

16:37.788 --> 16:39.779
Well, I'm fine.

16:41.292 --> 16:43.453
You were with Claudine?

16:45.796 --> 16:48.663
lt's none of your business
where | go or what I do.

16:48.841 --> 16:52.425
Sookie, for over 12 months
l was so empty.

16:52.595 --> 16:54.460
It was as if....

16:56.641 --> 16:58.506
I thought you had died.

16:58.726 --> 17:01.138
Well, I knew you weren't dead.

17:01.312 --> 17:03.974
-Eric, not now.
-I never lost hope.

17:04.148 --> 17:07.436
-Don't you have an obligation?
-I don't think so. Pam can handle it.

17:07.610 --> 17:09.692
-They want you.
-I appreciate your concern.

17:09.862 --> 17:11.363
Eric, go!

17:13.324 --> 17:15.440
Apparently I have to go.

17:15.618 --> 17:16.983
But understand this.

17:17.161 --> 17:19.868
Everyone who claims to love you...

17:20.039 --> 17:22.826
...your friends, your brother...

17:23.000 --> 17:26.163
...even Bill Compton,
they all gave up on you.

17:26.337 --> 17:30.000
I never did.

17:33.636 --> 17:35.001
Nice paint.

17:36.556 --> 17:39.093
[SIREN WAILS]

17:48.192 --> 17:51.184
-You have gotta be shitting me.
-Happy to see you too, Andy.

17:51.362 --> 17:54.854
-Jeez. Are you all right?
-Yeah, I'm safe, sound.

17:55.032 --> 17:58.866
-We all thought--
-They all thought that I had killed you.

17:59.036 --> 18:01.493
When you're up to it,
come on down to the station.

18:01.664 --> 18:04.701
We'll get your statement,
track down whoever it was that took you.

18:04.875 --> 18:06.490
-Nobody took me.
-What?

18:06.669 --> 18:09.206
-I wasn't kidnapped.
-Don't tell me you skipped town.

18:09.380 --> 18:11.917
You know how many man hours
I put into looking for you?

18:12.091 --> 18:13.376
Hey, take it easy, Andy.

18:13.551 --> 18:16.543
We dragged the fucking lake for you!
Where the hell did you go?

18:16.721 --> 18:19.758
-Hey.
-She was working for me.

18:19.932 --> 18:22.218
-Vampire business.
-What?

18:22.393 --> 18:24.850
Are you kidding me?
What kind of vampire business?

18:25.021 --> 18:27.433
For a year, you swore
you had no idea where she was.

18:27.607 --> 18:31.020
I deeply apologize
for misleading you, sheriff.

18:32.570 --> 18:35.733
Too many human lives would be at risk
if I did not keep it a secret.

18:35.906 --> 18:38.864
Now, as you can see,
Miss Stackhouse is unharmed.

18:39.035 --> 18:40.275
I'm back. I'm fine.

18:40.453 --> 18:43.570
I will come down to the office tomorrow
and I will explain it all.

18:43.748 --> 18:46.285
And I will repay the costs
of the search effort...

18:46.459 --> 18:49.747
...as soon as you issue
a statement clearing my name.

18:49.920 --> 18:52.411
Obviously, I did not kill her.

18:54.050 --> 18:56.917
For 13 straight months
I've had that open case on my books.

18:57.094 --> 19:00.211
If it weren't for you,
this year's Louisiana Safe Streets plaque...

19:00.389 --> 19:03.756
...would be on my wall
and not fucking Webster Parish!

19:03.934 --> 19:05.435
All right, that's enough!

19:05.603 --> 19:08.140
Andy, this ain't nothing
we can't get into tomorrow.

19:08.356 --> 19:10.938
-You owe me a plaque!
-Get in the car.

19:11.108 --> 19:13.565
You get in the car.

19:21.118 --> 19:23.450
I know I've lost an entire year...

19:23.621 --> 19:27.785
...and I know you must have been
worried for me...

19:27.958 --> 19:31.121
...but in my mind...

19:31.295 --> 19:36.289
...it's only an hour ago that you broke
my heart into a million pieces.

19:36.467 --> 19:38.628
I understand.

19:38.803 --> 19:40.919
You're safe.

19:41.097 --> 19:43.179
That's all that matters.

19:43.391 --> 19:46.474
-|'|| leave you be.
-Oh, no.

19:47.895 --> 19:49.806
That's good.

19:50.690 --> 19:52.646
I'm glad you're okay with....

19:54.944 --> 19:57.435
I'm glad you're okay. Yeah.

19:58.489 --> 20:00.320
Good night, Sookie.

20:13.504 --> 20:15.995
-You using again?
-What? No.

20:17.341 --> 20:20.925
I had maybe one drop this morning,
but it's gone. I'm out.

20:32.189 --> 20:34.020
You're out now.

20:42.700 --> 20:44.531
LAFAYETTE:
Five minutes.

20:47.371 --> 20:48.907
The woman who leads that group...

20:49.081 --> 20:52.323
...l've never seen anybody
more hooked in to the magic inside of her.

20:52.501 --> 20:55.038
-|t'|| be good for you.
-Ten months.

20:55.212 --> 20:58.204
Ten good motherfucking months
I've gone without a vision...

20:58.382 --> 21:01.874
...and now you want me to go hang out
with a bunch of witches. In a coven.

21:02.052 --> 21:03.087
It's not a coven.

21:03.262 --> 21:05.878
First it was your meditation group.
Then it was...

21:06.056 --> 21:09.048
-|t's different, completely different.
-...the Dallas Pagan Fair.

21:09.226 --> 21:10.887
Five minutes.

21:11.061 --> 21:12.892
Ten if they got drinks.

21:20.863 --> 21:23.900
Smell like where old air fresheners
go to die.

21:24.074 --> 21:26.065
You'll get used to it.

21:26.410 --> 21:28.901
Now, they're cool. Trust me.

21:29.622 --> 21:32.113
They even got a beaded curtain.

21:34.752 --> 21:37.915
LAFAYETTE:
Oh, hell no.

21:38.255 --> 21:41.247
[MARNIE CHANTING]

21:47.765 --> 21:49.255
Hi.

21:49.433 --> 21:51.264
HOLLY: Look who's here.
-So sorry we're late.

21:51.435 --> 21:54.302
Oh, no. You haven't missed anything.
Is this your--?

21:54.522 --> 21:56.808
Yeah, this is my partner.
Lafayette, this is Katie.

21:57.024 --> 21:59.060
-Hi.
-Finally broke him down, huh?

21:59.235 --> 22:00.941
I've been trying for ages.

22:01.111 --> 22:03.102
We are so glad that you joined us.

22:03.280 --> 22:04.941
Oh, no. Wait. I'm not--

22:05.115 --> 22:07.447
Did you tell them I was joining?

22:08.619 --> 22:12.282
That's Marnie.
We'll introduce you to her later.

22:12.456 --> 22:14.117
She look like she could use a nap.

22:14.291 --> 22:17.124
Oh, no. She's transported herself
to another plane.

22:17.294 --> 22:19.159
That's how she can contact
the spirits of the dead.

22:19.338 --> 22:22.455
-Does she ever find anybody?
-We|l, it's like fishing.

22:22.633 --> 22:25.625
Cast your line, sometimes
you get a response, sometimes you don't.

22:25.803 --> 22:28.044
On nights we don't,
there's always vodka.

22:29.139 --> 22:31.346
Greatest witch ever, huh?

22:31.559 --> 22:33.470
Don't be an asshole.

22:51.829 --> 22:53.319
Me?

22:54.999 --> 22:56.990
But what she want me for?

22:58.627 --> 23:00.333
Go on. It's okay.

23:04.174 --> 23:06.335
[MARNIE GRUNTING]

23:07.511 --> 23:08.671
LAFAYETTE:
How y'all doing?

23:18.856 --> 23:23.896
Did you ever know anyone named--?
Named Edith?

23:24.111 --> 23:26.193
No.

23:26.363 --> 23:28.024
Never. I'm pretty sure.

23:28.198 --> 23:31.361
Maybe in a short form? Edie?

23:31.535 --> 23:34.402
No. But keep guessing.

23:34.663 --> 23:37.530
-You'll get one right eventually.
HOLLY: Wait. Hold on.

23:41.420 --> 23:42.705
Eddie?

23:44.924 --> 23:46.164
Could be.

23:46.342 --> 23:47.377
It's a common name.

23:47.551 --> 23:50.213
-You lose someone by that name recently?
-We lost touch.

23:50.387 --> 23:52.924
